{"lemma":"ضَبْعُ","slug":"ضَبْعُ","root":"ض.ب.ع","root_slug":"ض-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ب-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n25509","n25512"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hyena"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṣ́abuʕ-. Cognate with Biblical Hebrew צָבוֹעַ (ṣɔḇóaʿ)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25509","headword_ar":"ضَبْعٌ","root":"DbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDud","text_ar":"عَضُد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a quadruped], (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altogether:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with its flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inner side thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or (so in some copies of the K, but in others “ and, ”) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"armpit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, of the upper part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDud","text_ar":"عَضُد"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is between the armpit and the half of the former:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) it is of man and of other than man: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDobaAEN","text_ar":"اَضْبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abad~a DabEayohi","text_ar":"اَبَدَّ ضَبعَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bd","text_ar":"بد"},{"kind":"text","text":",] speaking of a man praying. (O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*otu biDaboEaYo fulaAnK falamo A^ufaAriqohu","text_ar":"اَخَذْتُ بِضَبْعَىْ فُلَانٍ فَلَمْ اُفَارِقْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madadotu biDaboEayohi","text_ar":"مَدَدْتُ بِضَبْعَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I seized the middle of the upper arms of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and did not relinquish him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lth, O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*abahu biDaboEayohi","text_ar":"جَذَبَهُ بِضَبْعَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He raised him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set him up, and rendered his name famous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a biDaboEayohi","text_ar":"اَخَذَ بِضَبْعَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a biDaboEayohi","text_ar":"مَدَّ بِضَبْعَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hill such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamap","text_ar":"اَكَمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is black and somewhat oblong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba bihi DaboEFA laboEFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ بِهِ ضَبْعًا لَبْعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATilFA","text_ar":"بَاطِلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took it away with a false pretence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in play,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sport"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K, TA;) namely, a thing; (O, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laboEFA","text_ar":"لَبْعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an imitative sequent. (TA.)       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuEN","text_ar":"ضَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A5-  And see what here next follows."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","Lth","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n25512","headword_ar":"ضَبُعٌ","root":"DbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaboEN","text_ar":"ضَبْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) the former of the dial. of Keys and the latter of the dial. of Temeem, (Msb,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female hyena;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hyena, male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain animal of prey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuEN","text_ar":"سَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but see what follows,]) (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worst,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most abominable, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAE","text_ar":"سِبَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the wolf, except that, when it runs, it is as though it were lame, wherefore it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEarojaA='u","text_ar":"العَرْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it flees from him who holds in his hand a colocynth: [and they assert that] the dogs bark not at him who retains with him its teeth: if its skin is bound upon the belly of her that is pregnant, she casts not her young: if seed is measured in a measure covered with its skin, the seed-produce is secure from the banes thereof: and the application of its gall-bladder as a collyrium sharpens the sight: (K:) it is not reckoned among the hostile animals to which the appellation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuEN","text_ar":"سَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied, wherefore the Sunneh allows that its flesh may be eaten, and requires that a compensation be made for it [by the sacrifice of a ram] if it be smitten [and killed] in the sacred territory by a person in the state of ihrám: (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuEN","text_ar":"سَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the word is of the fem. gender, (S, * Mgh, * O, * Msb, K, *) and is [said to be] applied peculiarly to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"being called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabaAEiynu","text_ar":"ضَبَاعِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) but AHát disapproved this pl.; (O;) and the female is called [also] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnapN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnaAtN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnapN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has not been heard applied"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1767},{"kind":"text","text":"to the female, but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuEN","text_ar":"ضَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only, and it seems that J has mentioned"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnapN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to the female from his having supposed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnaAtN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnapN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", whereas it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaAlaAtN","text_ar":"رِجَالَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jimaAlaAtN","text_ar":"جِمَالَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IB in a marginal note in one of my copies of the S:) but some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuEN","text_ar":"ضَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaboEN","text_ar":"ضَبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaboEapN","text_ar":"ضَبْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus with a quiescent letter: (Msb:) or, accord. to Ibn-'Abbád, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuEapN","text_ar":"ضَبُعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and its pl. [or rather the coll. gen. n.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuEN","text_ar":"ضَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabaEapN","text_ar":"ضَبَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not allowable: (S, K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuEN","text_ar":"ضَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaboEN","text_ar":"ضَبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDobuEN","text_ar":"اَضْبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) a pl. of pauc., (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DibaAEN","text_ar":"ضِبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the former is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaboEN","text_ar":"ضَبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and the latter is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuEN","text_ar":"ضَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) and is of the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DubuEN","text_ar":"ضُبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) as though this were pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DibaAEN","text_ar":"ضِبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AAF, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DubEN","text_ar":"ضُبعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DubuEN","text_ar":"ضُبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DubuEaAtN","text_ar":"ضُبُعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DubuwEapN","text_ar":"ضُبُوعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA [in which it is indicated that this last is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaboEN","text_ar":"ضَبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) and [quasi-pl. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDobaEapN","text_ar":"مَضْبَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amodaru","text_ar":"اَمْدَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiboEaAnN","text_ar":"ضِبْعَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaboEaAnu","text_ar":"ضَبْعَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] meaning, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male hyena"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inflated in the sides, big in the belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose sides are defiled with earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayolN jaAr~u AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"سَيْلٌ جَارُّ الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A torrent that draws forth the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuE","text_ar":"ضَبُع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its den;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K; in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAr~N AlS~abuEa","text_ar":"جارٌّ الصَّبُعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) hence meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a torrent produced by vehement rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dalojapu AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"دَلْجَةُ الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night-journeying of the hyena"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuE","text_ar":"ضَبُع"},{"kind":"text","text":"goes round about until midnight. (O, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yaxofaY *`lika EalaY AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"مَا يَخْفَى ذٰلِكَ عَلَى الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is not unapparent to the hyena"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DabuE","text_ar":"ضَبُع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is deemed stupid. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaqu mina AlD~abuEi","text_ar":"اَحْمَقُ مِنَ الضَّبُعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More stupid than the hyena"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov. (Meyd.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akalatohumu AlD~abuEu","text_ar":"اَكَلَتْهُمُ الضَّبُعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hyena devoured them"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of such as are held in mean estimation. (TA.) [But this may be otherwise rendered, as will be seen from what follows.] The saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tafar~aqato ganamiY yawomFA faqulotu lahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        yaA rab~i sal~iTo EalayohaA Al*iy^oba waAlD~abuEaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, dispersed themselves, one day, and I said in relation to them, O my Lord, set upon them the wolf and the hyena"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is said to mean an imprecation, that the wolf might kill the living of them, and the hyena devour the dead of them: or, as some say, it means that the speaker prayed for their safety; because, when both fall upon the sheep, or goats, each of them is diverted from the sheep, or goats, by the other; and thus means the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a DabuEFA wa*iy^obFA","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ ضَبُعًا وَذِيْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"send"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hyena and a wolf"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but the more probable meaning of the poet is an imprecation, the consequence of his anger and fatigue; and the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sal~iTo","text_ar":"سَلِّطْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"imports a notification of this meaning. (IB, TA.) ―         -b2-  [The pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~ibaAEu","text_ar":"الضِّبَاعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Numerous stars below"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAt naEo$","text_ar":"بَنَات نَعْش"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stars beta, gamma, delta and mu, of Bootes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star upon the head, and that upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the shoulders, and that upon the club, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaw~aA='","text_ar":"العَوَّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the name of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awolaAdu AlD~ibaAEi","text_ar":"اَوْلَادُ الضِّبَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is given to ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"θ, ι, κ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"λ,"},{"kind":"text","text":"app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with some other faint stars around these, of Bootes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stars upon the left hand and fore arm, and what surround the hand, of the faint stars, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaw~aA='","text_ar":"العَوَّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kzw.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~abuEu","text_ar":"الضَّبُعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The year of drought"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterility"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dearth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, IAth, O, Msb, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is destructive; severe:"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the fem. gender. (TA.) So in a verse cited in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AmA","text_ar":"اما"},{"kind":"text","text":"[voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aA","text_ar":"اَمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and again, with a variation, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~aA","text_ar":"اـِمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O. [But it is here said in the TA that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~abuEu","text_ar":"الضَّبُعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this instance means the animal of prey thus called.]) [Hence also,] it is related in a trad. of Aboo-Dharr, that a man said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA rasuwla A@ll~`hi A^akalatonaA AlD~abuEu","text_ar":"يَا رَسُولَ ا@للّٰهِ اَكَلَتْنَا الضَّبُعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O Apostle of God, the year of drought has consumed us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and he prayed for them. (TA.) [See also two other exs. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iy^obN","text_ar":"ذِيْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hunger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, O, TA.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) El-'Okeyleeyeh said, “ When a man whose evil, or mischief, we feared removed from us, we used to light a fire behind him: ” and being asked “ Why? ” she said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyataHaw~ala DabuEuhu maEahu","text_ar":"لِيَتَحَوَّلَ ضَبُعُهُ مَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In order that his evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief, might go away with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA","AAF"]}]}}